27/04/2007
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Minister of Justice and Law Enforcement Jozsef Petretei and counterparts from six Southeast European countries sealed a memorandum Thursday (April 26th) on co-operation in the fight against human and drug trafficking. After the ceremony, Petretei stressed that regional co-operation is an important prerequisite for fighting organised crime. Attending the two-day summit in Budapest were cabinet ministers from Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia, Serbia and Montenegro. (Fena, HINA, RTRS, DPA, Xinhua - 26/04/07)
